people.name: Lauren Pope
people.aboutText: Lauren Pope (born 29 September 1982) is an English television personality, actress, glamour model, DJ, music producer and entrepreneur. She has appeared in the ITV2 reality series The Only Way Is Essex from the first series in 2010. She was born and raised in Devon.

people.name: Amy Williams
people.aboutText:
Amy Joy Williams MBE (born 29 September 1982) is an English former skeleton racer and Olympic gold medallist.
Originally a runner, she began training in skeleton after trying the sport on a push-start track at the University of Bath.

people.name: Lisette Oropesa
people.aboutText: Lisette Oropesa (born September 29, 1983) is an first generation Cuban American operatic soprano. She has a wide repertoire that includes works from Gluck, Handel, Mozart, Rossini, Donizetti, Wagner, Verdi, Bizet, Massenet and Puccini. With her lyric coloratura soprano voice, she has performed roles in her native Spanish and English, as well as German, French and Italian.

people.name: Lisa Gormley
people.aboutText: Per Mertesacker (German pronunciation: [ˈpeːɐ̯ ˈmɛʁtəsʔakɐ]; born 29 September 1984) is a German professional footballer who plays as a centre back for Arsenal. He also played for the German national team but retired in August 2014 after winning the World Cup. Mertesacker is a youth product of Hannover 96 and he made his senior league debut in November 2003.

people.name: Per Mertesacker

people.name: Isha Sharvani

He is the twin brother of goalkeeper Henrik Moisander, and is the current captain of the national team of Finland.

His personal best time of 43.72, set 5 July 2015 in La Chaux-de-Fonds was an African Continental record and ranks him number 7 on the all time list, the 2nd fastest non-American. He is also a sub-20 200 metres runner.

Durant has won an NBA Most Valuable Player Award, four NBA scoring titles, the NBA Rookie of the Year Award, and an Olympic gold medal.

people.name: Justin Nozuka

people.name: Theo Adams

Martin began his career with Conference South (sixth-tier) club Eastleigh before turning professional with Southampton, then playing in League One, in 2009. people.name: Aaron Martin

people.name: Andrea Poli

people.name: Doug Brochu

Doug has an older brother, Chris Brochu, who is notable for his role as Ray Beech in the Disney Channel Original Movie Lemonade Mouth.

people.name: Lena Wermelt

Adem Ljajić (Serbian Cyrillic: Адем Љајић, Serbian pronunciation: [ǎːdɛm ʎǎːjitɕ]; born 29 September 1991) is a Serbian footballer who plays as an attacking midfielder or winger for Italian club Internazionale, on loan from Roma, and the Serbia national team.
Ljajić was set to join England's Manchester United from Partizan in January 2010, but they withdrew their option to sign him in December 2009. Instead, he joined Fiorentina for a reported fee of around €8 million in January 2010.

people.name: Adem Ljajić

Shuko (柊子, Shūko, born September 29, 1991, in Nara Prefecture, Japan) is a Japanese actress and lyricist who is represented by the talent agency, Act21. As a lyricist, she is nicknamed Shu.

people.name: Viktor Romanenkov

people.name: Halsey

In 2014, she signed her first recording contract with Astralwerks and released her debut EP, titled Room 93.

people.name: Britteny Cox
people.aboutText:
Britteny Cox (born 29 September 1994) is an Australian mogul skier. Growing up in the Victorian alpine resort of Falls Creek, Cox was born into a mogul skiing environment, with her family passionate mogul skiers.
Cox was the youngest athlete to compete at the Vancouver 2010 Olympic Winter Games.

people.name: Alice Matteucci

Alice Matteucci (born 29 September 1995 in Pescara) is an Italian tennis player.
Matteucci has won four singles and 11 doubles titles on the ITF tour in her career. On 23 November 2015, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 323.

people.aboutText: Don Juan Valentín de Todos los Santos Urdangarín y de Borbón (born 29 September 1999), in Basque: Joan Balentín Urdangarin de Borbon, is the eldest son of the Infanta Cristina of Spain and Iñaki Urdangarín. Juan is seventh in the line of succession to the Spanish Throne, after his mother.

Vera Lapko (Belarusian: Вера Лапко; born 29 September 1998) is a Belarusian tennis player.
Lapko has won one singles and one doubles title on the ITF tour in her career. On 29 June 2015, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 561.
